ops_sunbeam/relation_handlers.py.message:
Having worked through this review again I think that maybe we should do all assessment of status from one location - probably as part of the setup_event_handlers call.

At this point in time we can see everything needed to determine status:

a) is a relation present for mandatory relations

if the relation is missing and mandatory -> BlockedStatus()

b) is the relation complete

if the relation is incomplete -> WaitingStatus()

if the relation is complete -> ActiveStatus()

if a relation is removed from the model, the status will revert back to blocked if its mandatory.

for instances where we might have the need for 'storage' as in the glance charm, the charm code can look at its view of the world and tweak params to handler constructors as need be depending on what it sees.  This kinda makes the case for modelling the requirement for a relation in code rather than metadata.yaml

